timeline.bodyText:
To answer your question, I believe we should not report Issues for lines with @EJB or @Inject if bytecode is incomplete.
There is however an easy way to cover this, we simply have to check if there is any unknown annotation. To do so, I would simply modify method isTransientSerializableOrInjected as follow:
private static boolean isTransientSerializableOrInjected(VariableTree member) {
    if (ModifiersUtils.hasModifier(member.modifiers(), Modifier.TRANSIENT) || (isSerializable(member.type()) && !isSubtypeOfCollectionApi(member.type().symbolType()))) {
      return true;
    }
    SymbolMetadata metadata = member.symbol().metadata();
    return metadata.isAnnotatedWith("javax.inject.Inject")
      || metadata.isAnnotatedWith("javax.ejb.EJB")
      // we can not guarantee anything due to the presence of an unknown annotation
      || metadata.annotations().stream().anyMatch(annotationInstance -> annotationInstance.symbol().isUnknown());
  }

